text: The desert froglet (Crinia deserticola) is a species of frog. They are part of the Myobatrachidae family. They live in Australia. They live in savannas and deserts. == Other websites == * Hero J.-M; Horner P. & Retallick R. 2004. Crinia deserticola. 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species Downloaded on 23 July 2007.
